UK: Orange loss widens, but subscribers up.Orange loss widens, but subscribers up.Britain's mobile telephone operator Orange Plc said on Tuesday it now had over 600,000 subscribers, a gain on the 573,000 it reported at the end of June.The news came as the company announced a pre-tax loss of 125.2 million pounds ($193.6 million) in line with market consensus for the six months to June 30, but up from 88.8 million previously. At the same time however Orange's sales in the first half more than doubled to 256.5 million from 100 million pounds.